Credit Suisse First Boston Mortgage Review • Mortgage Insider   HomeCalculatorsDefinitionsAsk QuestionTutorialsReviewsRate QuotesCompareArchiveThe Mortgage InsiderGet the Inside Scoop on Mortgages! Get 4 Free Quotes Now! Powered by SecureRights You are here: Home / Reviews / Credit Suisse First Boston Mortgage ReviewCredit Suisse First Boston Mortgage Review    Credit Suisse First Boston retails mortgages for private clients and is huge in the mortgage-backed securities markets through their subsidiary, Credit Suisse First Boston Mortgage Securities Corp. We uncovered 2 phone numbers, a website, and helpful tips on how to shop for a mortgage online at the bottom of the page.Credit Suisse First Boston Mortgage ReviewAccording to their website:Credit Suisse First Boston’s private mortgage products are diverse.  Some of the most ingenious program I’ve ever come across this company reserves for the super rich.  Programs like their, Construction Loan, Fix Mortgage, Flex Rollover Mortgage, Adjustable-Rate Mortgage, Mix Mortgage, Flex Mortgage, Start-Up Bonus Mortgage, Minergie Mortgage, Pension Mortgage…have a unique set of terms and serve a unique mortgage consumer.CSFB acquired mortgage servicer, Select Portfolio Servicing, Inc. (SPS) in August of 2005.  SPS is front and center in the foreclosure crisis as they are now being looked to for help in implementing the Obama Plan to help foreclosure victims with loan modifications.Note: Read Our Top Five Mortgage Complaints!   Additional DBA Names: Credit Suisse Credit Suisse First Boston CS First Boston First Boston Corporation Credit Suisse First Boston Mortgage Securities Corp. Select Portfolio ServicingCredit Suisse First Boston Website and Phone ContactsWebsite:  www.credit-suisse.comPhone: (212) 325-2000Additional Phone Numbers:  (212) 325-7149Fax Number:  (212) 325-8217Address: 11 Madison Avenue, New York, NY 10010  Credit Suisse First Boston Complaints and RatingsAnd you may want to look at the BBB for complaints and ratings.  Keep in mind the banks and credit unions have a rating and number of complaints for the company as a whole not just the mortgage department.  On nmls.com, you can check make sure your Credit Suisse First Boston loan officer is active and registered and for mortgage companies, (not banks or credit unions) you can see if any lawsuits/regulatory actions have been taken.Good Luck!Note: Compare Mortgage Rates of local lenders now!Get a mortgage rates quote from 4 legit lenders Free...Click Here!Author: The Mortgage InsiderCredit Suisse First Boston Mortgage Review was last modified:  August 26th, 2015 by The Mortgage InsiderRelated PostsSelect Portfolio Servicing ReviewBoston Private Bank & Trust…East Boston Savings Bank Mortgage ReviewFiled Under: ReviewsClick Next To Visit Lender's Site   About The Mortgage InsiderSearch Our Site…      Popular PostsEmbrace Home Loans ReviewCredit Score: How Important Is It? Mortgage Rate TrendsGreen Tree Servicing Review What is an Underwriting Fee? Hardship Letter MistakesDivorce Mortgage MistakesMortgage Payoff Amount Vs BalanceRecent Posts Access National Mortgage Review Stafford Savings Bank Mortgage Review Verve – CitizensFirst Mortgage Review EVB Mortgage Review Stearns Bank Mortgage ReviewQ&A’sForeclosure Q&AMortgage Q&AReal Estate Q&ARefinancing Q&AJoin Us On…PagesContactCategory & Archive PageTestimonialsPost SiteMap Return to top of pageCopyright © 2017 · Prose Theme on Genesis Framework · WordPress · Log in     















